Certainly! Below is a simple C++ program that takes input for the taste, texture, and country of origin of bitter chocolate and outputs these attributes in three words.

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string taste;
    std::string texture;
    std::string country;

    std::cout << "Enter the taste of the bitter chocolate: ";
    std::getline(std::cin, taste);

    std::cout << "Enter the texture of the bitter chocolate: ";
    std::getline(std::cin, texture);

    std::cout << "Enter the country of origin for the cocoa beans: ";
    std::getline(std::cin, country);

    std::cout << "\nChocolate Description in Three Words:\n";
    std::cout << taste << ", " << texture << ", " << country << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

### How to Use the Program:

1. Compile the program using a C++ compiler, like `g++`:

   ```
   g++ -o chocolate_description chocolate_description.cpp
   ```

2. Run the compiled program:

   ```
   ./chocolate_description
   ```

3. Follow the prompts to input the taste, texture, and country of origin.

4. The program will output the description of the chocolate in three words.
